author: Inside Edition
description: A New York squirrel is hoping for a holiday miracle after being rescued from a dire situation. On Christmas Eve, a team of first responders used olive oil to free the animal after she became stuck in a dumpster. Because the squirrel was in poor condition, Dani Wood from All Creatures Great and Small Wildlife Rehabilitation was called in to provide care. Dani named the squirrel Holly and is now doing everything possible to help her survive. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: New York Squirrel Rescued From Dumpster On Christmas Eve

author: Inside Edition
description: Outgoing U.S. Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene was once a close ally of Donald Trump, before having a major fallout with the president. Now Greene is taking on the women surrounding Trump. In a recent interview with New York Magazine, Greene decried their "sexualization," and called them out for the way they dress and for cosmetic procedures she claims they underwent. The Georgia-based Greene is set to leave her seat in early January of 2026.
title: Marjorie Taylor Greene Takes On Women In Trump's Circle

author: Inside Edition
description: Last month, the nation's heart broke once again for the Kennedy family, when Tatiana Schlossberg revealed in an essay in the New Yorker that she had terminal cancer. Schlossberg is the daughter of Caroline Kennedy, and the granddaughter of President John F. Kennedy and Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis. In her essay, Tatiana wrote that doctors told her she had maybe one more year to live. It turned out to be just weeks, as today her family shared the sad news that she had died from leukemia.
title: JFK's Granddaughter Dies At 35

author: Inside Edition
description: Tomorrow night is New Year's Eve. There will be celebrations around the world, but perhaps nowhere bigger than that in New York City's Times Square. Inside Edition's Steven Fabian was there as the iconic ball drop got a test run. The first big New Year's celebration in Times Square was in 1907; on that occasion, the descending wooden ball contained 100 light bulbs. Today's ball, containing Waterford crystals, has more than 32,000 lights.
title: Sneak Preview Of Times Square New Years Ball Drop

author: Inside Edition
description: It's that time of year to be super careful out on the roads. Plunging temperatures have led to heavy snow and ice, making for perilous driving conditions. A couple and their two dogs learned this the hard way when their car slid off the road and ended up dangling above a ravine. The accident could have ended in disaster if not for a group of Good Samaritans who came to their rescue. People formed a human chain to bring the family to safety.
title: Human Chain Rescues Family Trapped In Ravine

author: Inside Edition
description: A massive outbreak of an especially virulent 'super flu' has gripped England, and now the virus has crossed the Atlantic. There are lots of questions: how do you know you have it? And is it too late to get a flu shot? Symptoms include severe aches, fatigue, persistent cough, headache, sore throat, and chills. Inside Edition's Jim Moret spoke with a woman who not only has the super flu, but is also 20 weeks pregnant.
title: Doctors Warn Of 'Super Flu' Outbreak

author: Inside Edition
description: Where is Camila Mendoza Olmes? There's still no sign of the Texas teenager who walked out of her home on Christmas Eve in her pajama bottoms and never came home. While cops look for clues, there are also citizen sleuths on the case, sharing any tidbit of information they can find online. Authorities announced that Camila was in “imminent danger.” Her family and friends hold out hope for her safe return.
title: Internet Sleuths Try To Find Missing Teen Camila Mendoza Olmes

author: Inside Edition
description: Cops say a Florida man killed his wife in an argument about watching last week's big game. Jason Kenney was enjoying the San Francisco 49ers–Indianapolis Colts clash at his family's home in Lakeland. He even posted a photo of the snacks he had set up for the game. But as the game was winding up, and it was clear the 49ers were certain to win, something happened. Kenney's wife Crystal suggested they watch what she was watching on TV. What followed was a terrible argument. To support Crystal's family, please visit their GoFundMe: https://www.gofundme.com/f/support-for-crystals-children-after-her-tragic-loss
title: Florida Man Kills Wife Over 'Monday Night Football': Police

author: Inside Edition
description: The brazen theft of two vintage instruments happened at Lark's Music in Teaneck, New Jersey.
title: Suspect Returns Stolen Mandolins #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A suspect thought he could get away from police in a golf cart, but he didn't know how determined these cops were to catch him. Bodycam from Sandy Springs police officers in Georgia show the hot pursuit. They say the person they were after had warrants out for his arrest. When he saw them coming, they say he jumped into the nearest vehicle to get away, which happened to be a golf cart. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cops Catch Up With Suspect Who Tried To Flee In Golf Cart

author: Inside Edition
description: The mystery deepens in the urgent search for 19-year-old Camila Mendoza Olmes, who disappeared on December 24th. Authorities now claim she is in "imminent danger."
title: Where Is Missing Teen Camila Mendoza Olmes? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A sinkhole swallowed up a parked car in Turkey and all people could do was watch. Turkish media says it happened in a parking area not far from a stream. The soil seemed to shift open under the vehicle, creating a large enough opening to take the whole car. It was a sight to watch, especially because the car was unoccupied. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Sinkhole Swallows Parked Car As People Watch Helplessly

author: Inside Edition
description: The new year may be just around the corner, but fears of terrorism are putting a damper on festivities across the globe.
title: Jitters Mute New Years Celebrations #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: In January 2025, former "first buddy" Elon Musk caught heat on the first day of Donald Trump's second term after he made a gesture that some thought resembled a Nazi salute. In April, Pope Francis died, ending a 12 year papacy. His replacement stunned the world. After a two-day conclave, Cardinal Robert Prevost from Chicago became the first ever American pope. He is now known as Pope Leo XIV. In the summer, Karen Read emerged victorious after a two-month trial.
title: Big Newsmakers In 2025 Included Pope Leo XIV, Karen Read, And Elon Musk

author: Inside Edition
description: The Tennessee Highway Patrol says a distressed woman was standing on a highway overpass above the Holston River, when officers intervened. Bodycam shows an officer pull her back, saving a life this holiday season.
title: Woman Pulled Back From Edge Of Bridge #shorts
